d as the students sitting in this great hall sands said but as different as they are these great deeds have something in common they all relied on the leadership of a purdue boilermaker   the late neil armstrong the first person to walk on the moon was such an example sands said neil tended to understate his accomplishments  he was a humble man which made him a great leader sands said when he returned from his historic moonwalk neil talked about helping the needy and feeding millions of hungry people around the world  he said it s going to take an international approach far beyond any cooperative effort ever seen in history sands said armstrong had the vision of a great leader because he saw a cause larger than himself and that leadership is about learning how to pull people or ideas together to focus on a clear objective   people become leaders because they want to make something better just as we once built a building one brick higher he said  sands wished the graduates a safe flight and happy landing as they launch into the next phase of their journeys photo gallery of the december 2012 commencement ceremonies '
